        <font size='4'><b>LORETTA'S WINTER STYLE </b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090115.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, January 15, 2009</b> &mdash;
    Winter is officially in full swing, so once again it&#039;s time to bundle up. If you&#039;re like us&mdash;you&#039;ve probably been looking through your closet, searching for that perfect, warm-yet-stylish cold weather outfit. <br><br>Luckily, we were able to catch up with Millsberry&#039;s expert of all things stylish, Loretta Rivers, as she got ready for her <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">big winter fashion release</a>. <br><br>Over at <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">Wearhouse</a>, it was immediately apparent that a large-scale fashion operation was underway. And Loretta was still scurrying around the store, giving her final approval to the new clothing, before sitting down for our exclusive interview.<br><br>Audrey Smythe-Wei: Wow, Loretta, it looks like you&#039;ve been busy!<br><br>Loretta Rivers: I know, right? I really put a lot into this <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">new line</a>. Hopefully that will come through in the clothes. <br>
<br>
Audrey Smythe-Wei: So, now that people in Millsberry are bundling up for winter, what advice can you give them about staying stylish?  <br><br>Loretta Rivers: Well, I think that most people think that having to bundle-up means you can&#039;t look stylish. But I think the more clothing you wear, the more style you can add to your look!<br><br>Audrey Smythe-Wei: That&#039;s true. I never thought of it like that before. What advice do you have as far as staying warm is concerned?<br><br>Loretta Rivers: The main thing you want to keep in mind about winter fashion is that layers are important. You&#039;ll stay warmer, and you&#039;ll be able to mix and match styles to create a bunch of cool looks. <br><br>Audrey Smythe-Wei: How do accessories factor into winter style? <br><br>Loretta Rivers: Accessories are another great part of winter fashion. To me, they might be the most important. There are so many ways to add to your outfit with simple things like a hat or scarf, and they keep you extra warm, too!<br><br>Audrey Smythe-Wei: If you had to pick one favorite winter fashion item, what would it be?<br><br>Loretta Rivers: That&#039;s tough. It&#039;s hard to pick just one, but if I had to pick, I would say leather jackets. I take that back. It&#039;s hard to beat a great sweater. Boots, also. I will always have a special place in my heart for boots. See, I told you I couldn&#039;t pick just one!  <br><br>Audrey Smythe-Wei: Well, fortunately for you, there are enough pieces in your new winter line to satisfy all your fashion urges. <br><br>Loretta Rivers: [Laughing] You&#039;re right about that! I just hope everyone else likes the clothes as much as I do. <br>
    </div>

